Dino Melaye, the spokesperson for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Presidential Campaign Organisation (PCO), has reacted to the attack on President Muhammadu Buhari in Kano State, saying the All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate, Bola Ahmed Tinubu is the masterminder. Information Nigeria had reported that some angry youths in Kano State, on Monday, hauled stones at the advance convoy of President Buhari and helicopter during an official visit to the state. READ ALSO: Dino Melaye Mocks Tinubu’s Outing At Chatham House However, the former lawmaker reacting to the development via his Twitter handle on Monday, claimed the attack was allegedly sponsored by Tinubu to embarrass President Buhari, adding that the plot to attack Buhari was orchestrated in Bourdillon, home of the APC flag bearer. He tweeted, “The fight between Tinubu and Buhari is entering a new dimension. The attack in Kano was properly coordinated and funded allegedly by Asiwaju. “The meeting to push Buhari to submission or face sponsored attack in the north was said to be hatched in Burdillon. Me, I am busy with Atiku.”